        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 2:21PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gunsight Peak, or 28 miles northwest of Fairfield, moving east at 45
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Paradise Peak around 230 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
